---
description: Regenerate committed media outputs after changing archive or project sources
globs:
  - media/project-sources/**/*
  - public/archive/**/*
  - scripts/generate-project-media.mjs
  - scripts/generate-archive-manifest.mjs
---

When you change anything under `media/project-sources/`, `public/archive/`, or edit either generator script, committed outputs must stay in sync.

Run:

```bash
pnpm generate:project-media
pnpm generate:archive-manifest
```

`pnpm generate:project-media` clears each `public/projects/<slug>/` before writing that project’s outputs (no leftover media/thumbnails for that slug). Use `pnpm generate:project-media:clean` to delete all of `public/projects` first (drops orphaned folders if you removed a project slug). CI `verify:generated` uses the clean variant.

Or either command alone if only one area changed. Then commit:

- `content/projects/generated-media.ts`
- `public/projects/**`
- `lib/generated/archive-manifest.ts`

CI runs `pnpm verify:generated` on push/PR so stale outputs fail the build.

After `pnpm install`, `prepare` points this repo at `.githooks` (`git config core.hooksPath .githooks`). The pre-commit hook only regenerates `lib/generated/archive-manifest.ts` when `public/archive/` or `scripts/generate-archive-manifest.mjs` is staged. Project media (`pnpm generate:project-media`) is intentionally not run on commit — run it yourself after changing `media/project-sources/`, and CI `verify:generated` enforces a clean full regen.
